Shared instructions for agents working on this Sphinx/MyST course-note repository.

## Documentation Structure

- Keep chapter content in Markdown under `docs/chapters/`.
- Prefer MyST syntax for math, cross-references, figures, and directives.
- Keep Sphinx configuration in `docs/conf.py`.
- Keep browser-side interactive code in static JavaScript files.
- For top-level or grouped chapter summary sections, use the heading `Summary`.

## MyST Conventions

- Use the repo-local `foldbox` directive for optional derivations.
- Use the `course-interactive` directive with `:data-example:` for implemented browser examples.
- Do not put large raw HTML, inline scripts, or implementation logic directly in chapter Markdown.
- Convert display math written as `$$ ... $$` to MyST math fences.

## Local Workflow

- Use `make html` for a documentation-only build.
- Use `make check` before handoff when changing chapters, navigation, Sphinx config, or static assets.
- Use the local HTTP server workflow when verifying interactive examples.
